The paper discusses the use of embeddings for entity mention disambiguation, relation inference, and deep question answering, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also proposes a new representation of types as hyper-rectangular regions, which falls under the category of computational geometry (cs.CG). The evaluation protocols discussed in the paper involve measuring the accuracy of transitive relation inference, which is relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL), databases (cs.DB), and information retrieval (cs.IR).
